wp:comment.wp:comment_content: Thanks! I really have no clue what I'm doing with this website. Adding tags now!

I find your work great! You should tag your posts so people will see them in their readers. You would then quickly gain more followers. Like this, your great paintings are nearly invisible because people looking for "art", "abstract", "painting" etc. will not see them.

You can search arround in the reader and look at other people's post for the tags they are using. I am always looking under "abstract" and "abstract art" cause that is what I like most. Another way to get attention is to like other people's posts. On your gravatar page, you should then add a link to your blog. People who want to find out who liked their stuff then have a way to find your blog. Commenting other people's posts is also effective. Another question: Do you sell your works? At what price range?
Thanks. And yes, I do sell my work. Ranging between $200-800.

To me, the paintings of Ashley Sullivan are mesmerizing. Some are pure abstracts, some are landscapes, some are cityscapes or show industrial motives, with varying degrees of abstraction. Many of them are magic for me. I had a hard time deciding which of these paintings to choose. Just have a look yourself.
Wow, I will. This one is amazing.
